        "subject": "LU-56 lnet: fix a race for in-creating peer",
        "message": "LU-56 lnet: fix a race for in-creating peer\n\nCreating peer will release lock and allocate memory, it's possible\nthat LNet is shuttingdown and destroyed everything in this small\nwindow (unlikely), so we need to add an extra refcount on peer table\nbefore allocating new peers to keep shutting down thread wait.\n\nThis patch also fixed a typo of locking funciton.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: If8945117885e59a6d2de5ad0dff24b41e7a16bba\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
